Create a Live Connection to Google BigQuery

Explore data directly in Google BigQuery

To create live connections to Google BigQuery: Enable CRM Analytics Direct Data for external data sources
To explore data directly in Google BigQuery: Explore External Data Directly

Create the Live Connection

In CRM Analytics, click the gear icon and select Data Manager.

Click Manage Dataflows.

Click Connect tab.

Click Connect to Data.

Click Live Connections.

Click Add Connection.

Click Google BigQuery Direct Connector and enter its settings.

When done, click Save or Save and Create Dataset.

Create Live Datasets for a Google BigQuery Source Table

After creating the live connection, enable a live dataset for the connection.

In the data manager, click the Data tab.

On the Live Datasets tab, click Create Dataset. Select the Google BigQuery connection and enable a Google BigQuery source table that is available with the connection.

Name the live dataset and assign it to a CRM Analytics app.

Google BigQuery Live Connections Settings

Setting	DESCRIPTION
Connection Name	Identifies the live connection.
Developer Name	API name for the connection.
Description	Description of the connection for internal use.
Client Email	Enter the client_email value from the JSON file.
Private Key	Enter the private_key value from the JSON file.
Project ID	Enter the project_id value from the JSON file.
Storage Path	Optional setting. Path in Google Cloud Storage where a local stage file is created to store the data temporarily.
Schema	Google BigQuery schema whose data you want to explore with the connection.
Region ID	Optional setting. Enter the data location of the live Google BigQuery dataset if the location isnâ€™t in North America.
Use Storage API	Optional setting. If True, uses the Google BigQuery Storage Read API.
